        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 4:45PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 445 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Vandiver to near Chelsea to near West
Blocton. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Country Club Estates, Alpine Bay Resort, Columbiana, Shelby Shores,
Gantts Quarry, Highway 145 and CR 46, Childersburg, American Village,
Westover, Camp Branch, Alabaster Veterans Park, Maylene, Varnons,
Chelsea, Mignon, Sylacauga Municipal Airport, Cedar Creek, Oak Grove,
Wilton, and Alpine.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
